<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,919,1952]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1892,1917]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Description.</emphasis>
Body stellate (R:r=3.15–3.36), arms triangular (
<figureCitation box="[887,969,1892,1917]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="63.[151,250,1707,1729]" captionTargetBox="[166,1417,219,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@63.[151,1436,195,1685]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURE 22. Paraferdina plakos n. sp. A – C: Paratype, MNHN-IE- 2007 - 1099. Scale Bar = 1.8 mm. A. Abactinal surface. B. Abactinal and superomarginal detail. C. Actinal surface. D – F: Holotype MNHN-IE- 2013 - 6604, Scale Bar = 6.0 mm. D. Abactinal surface. E. Superomarginal and abactinal detail. F. Actinal surface." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/583214/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
A) to more blunt-tipped and finger-like in shape (
<figureCitation box="[230,311,1927,1952]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="63.[151,250,1707,1729]" captionTargetBox="[166,1417,219,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@63.[151,1436,195,1685]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURE 22. Paraferdina plakos n. sp. A – C: Paratype, MNHN-IE- 2007 - 1099. Scale Bar = 1.8 mm. A. Abactinal surface. B. Abactinal and superomarginal detail. C. Actinal surface. D – F: Holotype MNHN-IE- 2013 - 6604, Scale Bar = 6.0 mm. D. Abactinal surface. E. Superomarginal and abactinal detail. F. Actinal surface." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/583214/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
D). Body stout. Granulated tissue layer covers body surface.
</paragraph>
